In order to successfully target the Chinese and Islamic markets, new IT-based start-ups should first do in-depth market research to identify their unique requirements and preferences. This may include researching the morals and beliefs of Muslim customers as well as Chinese consumers' tastes and technical advancements. To expand its reputation and reach in these regions, the start-up would also need to form partnerships with regional companies and influencers. Language localization and adherence to local rules and legislation are two factors to take into account. 